# Normalize line endings: text files are stored as LF in the repo and checked
# out as LF (this project's dev + deploy are Linux). Prevents the recurring
# CRLF churn that appeared on edits to files with legacy CRLF endings.
#
# Renormalization is incremental: existing CRLF-committed files convert to LF
# the first time they are `git add`ed with these rules active. A full one-time
# `git add --renormalize .` is deferred until in-flight refactor branches merge,
# to avoid mass merge conflicts.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never touch line endings.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.svg text
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.xlsx binary
*.xls binary
*.zip binary
